parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates on the instrument panel
the brake pedal feels stiff or hard to press
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the brakes fail to respond
the vehicle swerves or loses control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to suddenly accelerate or lose control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
loss of vehicle control
air shocks failing
air suspension system failing to keep the vehicle up
front suspension air strut cracking
front of the vehicle dropping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to slip or hesitate when shifting gears, leading to loss of power, reduced acceleration, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
particularly in 3rd and 4th gears
loss of power
reduced acceleration
inability to shift into gear.
